{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/chief-digital-officers-real-value-of-just-a-hype-c3da9d054472", "time": 1683001174.594007, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/chief-digital-officers-real-value-of-just-a-hype-c3da9d054472/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "How to build a data-driven culture | by Luca Condosta (PhD) | Towards Data Science", "h1": "How to build a data-driven culture", "description": "Data as the new Oil. But are the CDOs just a hype or can bring real value to business?"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.economist.com/leaders/2017/05/06/the-worlds-most-valuable-resource-is-no-longer-oil-but-data", "anchor_text": "Economist", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.gartner.com/smarterwithgartner/3-top-take-aways-from-the-gartner-chief-data-officer-survey/", "anchor_text": "research", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://www.amazon.it/bilancio-sociale-dazienda-tecniche-redazione/dp/8821727076/ref=sr_1_14?__mk_it_IT=%C3%85M%C3%85%C5%BD%C3%95%C3%91&dchild=1&keywords=bilancio+sociale&qid=1585989807&s=books&sr=1-14", "anchor_text": "Sustainability reporting", "paragraph_index": 17}, {"url": "https://www.amazon.com/Natuzzi-Italian-Harmony-Luca-Condosta-ebook/dp/B079Z653TX/ref=sr_1_3?dchild=1&keywords=natuzzi&qid=1585989896&sr=8-3", "anchor_text": "Natuzzi \u2014 The Italian Harmony Maker", "paragraph_index": 17}], "all_paragraphs": ["A famous article from the Economist equalized data and the value of Oil. Gartner\u2019s research shows how the number of Chief Data Officers is globally growing.", "But how can you build a real data-driven culture in your organization? Chief Data Officer (CDO) can bring real value or are just a hype?", "Let\u2019s be honest: when you start working with data, unless you operate in a strong data-driven company (like Linkedin, Facebook), your first role is to evangelize the organization.", "You will spend a lot of time convincing people about the value of data, showing them what is your data gap in terms of quality and business capabilities.", "For example, sliding and dicing your revenue streams based on multiple variables, analyzing in-depth part of your costs or showing how you can reduce the complexity of your operation if your data is properly maintained and high quality.", "What I noticed in my experience is that, if you can break this wall, the real data journey can start. People will start contacting you from the inside of the organization asking if there\u2019s a possibility to use data to achieve certain business needs. This is the first sign showing you that all work done to educate your organization about the importance of data is starting to pay off.", "Once business people understand the potential of data, they will ask you to develop analytics and cross-functional projects, to answer the business questions.", "In this phase is critical for you to partner with your business to detect any other potential areas where the data you master can be leveraged.", "A quite successful project we launched, was about integrating HR and Finance data, to ensure alignment in the employee reporting and reducing errors and time wasted in reconciliations. Initially, everybody was skeptical but when the first pilot countries came out, the project became tangible and appreciated by key stakeholders in the organization.", "Business has data needs but maybe is not aware of it. Your role is to make sure this becomes visible.", "If you are lucky enough to get budget and business support, your journey can move full speed to unlock the value of data in your company through predictive analysis. Today this is not the case in many organizations since most of them are still educating the internal management on the business relevance of the topic.", "However, when data is at the core of the organization, the CDO is the one driving the agenda, smelling opportunities to use the company data in meetings, business reviews, functional steering committees, etc..", "Data becomes part of the way the company thinks and are no more a topic under the IT leadership.", "A real example, from my experience, is about using internal data to reduce complexity in the Finance function, leveraging on process mining tools and ERP connectivity to derive automatic KPIs and identifying duplication of activities so to trigger process automation and improvement initiatives. Benefits were in terms of speeding up operations, reducing errors and remove low value-added tasks from our employees.", "Now let\u2019s go through the seven insights I see to strengthen the position of the CDO.", "These pillars, in my experience, will boost the experience of the CDO and strengthen the data culture in an organization. They will make this position not just a hype but a real driver, unlocking the value of data in a disciplined way driving results and giving CDO the right dignity in the organization.", "\u201cWar is ninety percent information\u201d \u2014 Napoleon Bonaparte, French Military and Political Leader", "Luca Condosta(Ph.D.) is a finance professional with global experience in multinational businesses. Passionate for data, leadership, strategy and people. Author of two books (Sustainability reporting and Natuzzi \u2014 The Italian Harmony Maker) loves finding and sharing stories.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Finance professional with global experience in multinational businesses. Passionate for data, leadership, strategy and people."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fc3da9d054472&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fchief-digital-officers-real-value-of-just-a-hype-c3da9d054472&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav------